xplicitly-authorized certification scope.\n+- **Three required references** (`f8b8ed4`, `crates/editor-shell/src/render_frame_e2e_perf.rs`, `ai_handoffs/POSTV0-EDITOR-SHELL-PERF-HARNESS-001_EXEC_2026-05-14_21-51-40+0300.md`) â†’ all three present in each of the four modified docs (`git diff -- \u003cdoc\u003e | grep -c \u003cref\u003e` returns â‰¥ 1 for each `(doc, ref)` pair across all 12 combinations).\n+\n+**No Cargo commands run; no editor-shell perf harness execution; no fresh recorder-host measurements.** The TASK packet\u0027s `Constraints / Non-Goals` forbid all three; this EXEC dispatch honored that constraint.\n+\n+## Deviations from Task Packet\n+\n+None â€” execution stayed strictly within the Task Packet scope.\n+\n+Specifically:\n+- All four modified files are inside the `MAY edit` envelope.\n+- `plans/IMPLEMENTATION.md` was NOT edited (per TASK `MUST NOT edit`).\n+- No `crates/**`, `editor/**`, `kernel/**`, `runtime/**`, `tools/**`, `docs/**`, or any other `plans/**` path beyond `plans/BASELINE.md` was edited.\n+- `Cargo.toml` / `Cargo.lock` / `.gitignore` / `AI_DISPATCH_AUTOMATION.md` / `ai_handoffs/AI_HANDOFF_PROTOCOL.md` / `ai_handoffs/templates/**` were all untouched.\n+- No existing `ai_handoffs/` packet was edited, including the POSTV0 packet (read-only citation only).\n+- No new `ai_handoffs/` packet was added other than this dispatch\u0027s own EXEC packet (this file) and the dispatch\u0027s TASK packet that arrived with the dispatch.\n+- All four halt-condition triggers were absent: no `plans/IMPLEMENTATION.md` edit was needed; no source / test / bench / fixture / Cargo / schema / lint / automation / protocol-doc edit was needed; no new measurement row, copied recorder-host numbers, or new hard editor-shell thresholds were judged necessary to make the docs accurate; no Cargo command / release-only perf harness run / fresh recorder-host measurement was needed; the four allowed docs did not contain conflicting history that resisted the narrow current-dated-snapshot + narrow BASELINE.md wording approach.\n+\n+## Open Questions for Reviewer\n+\n+None mandatory. Two optional items for Reviewer attention if they want to scrutinize further:\n+\n+1. **Granularity of the BASELINE.md edit**: I chose to **append** a clearly-dated 2026-05-23 supersession paragraph directly below the existing 2026-05-14 Post-depth Gate A paragraph rather than **inline-edit** the \"What\u0027s still deferred: option (b) ...\" clause inside that 2026-05-14 paragraph. Rationale: the acceptance criterion \"If older dated context is retained, it must be explicitly framed as historical and superseded by `f8b8ed4`\" is satisfied by the new paragraph\u0027s explicit \"is HISTORICAL ONLY as of the 2026-05-14 paragraph that records it, and is SUPERSEDED by the post-v0 landing recorded here\" framing, without rewriting any pre-existing dated text. Reviewer may judge whether an inline strike-through or in-paragraph parenthetical would have been preferable; I judged the appended-paragraph form to be more conservative and more clearly attributed to ISSUE-118.\n+2. **No measurement numbers copied**: I deliberately did NOT include the POSTV0 EXEC packet\u0027s recorder-host P95 / P50 / worst-sample numbers anywhere in the four docs, per the TASK packet\u0027s explicit acceptance criterion forbidding that. The new BASELINE.md / Status.md / HANDOFF.md / change.md entries record only existence, path, commit, and packet provenance â€” exactly what the TASK packet allowed.\n+\n+## Worktree State\n+\n+- Tracked files: 4 modified â€” `plans/BASELINE.md`, `Status.md`, `HANDOFF.md`, `change.md`. No other tracked file modified.\n+- Untracked items:\n+  - `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-118_TASK_2026-05-23_12-04-16+0300.md` (the dispatch\u0027s TASK packet â€” arrived with the dispatch; not authored by the Executor).\n+  - `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-118_TASK_2026-05-23_12-04-16+0300.meta.json` (automation sidecar for the TASK packet).\n+  - `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-118_EXEC_2026-05-23_