        "patch":  "@@ -0,0 +1,184 @@\n+# Task Packet\n+\n+DISPATCH_ID: ISSUE-118\n+AUTHOR: Planner / OpenAI Codex\n+TIMESTAMP: 2026-05-23_12-04-16+0300\n+RELATED_FILES:\n+- plans/BASELINE.md\n+- Status.md\n+- HANDOFF.md\n+- change.md\n+- ai_handoffs/POSTV0-EDITOR-SHELL-PERF-HARNESS-001_EXEC_2026-05-14_21-51-40+0300.md\n+STATUS: OPEN\n+\n+## Goal\n+\n+Reconcile stale editor-shell perf-harness deferral text that still describes the\n+non-winit editor-shell render-frame perf harness as outstanding, even though the\n+POSTV0 editor-shell perf-harness dispatch landed it at commit `f8b8ed4` via\n+`crates/editor-shell/src/render_frame_e2e_perf.rs`. This is a documentation-only\n+history reconciliation for GitHub issue #118: preserve the old dated records as\n+history, add a current dated record that supersedes the stale deferral wording,\n+and cross-reference\n+`ai_handoffs/POSTV0-EDITOR-SHELL-PERF-HARNESS-001_EXEC_2026-05-14_21-51-40+0300.md`.\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+### MAY edit\n+- plans/BASELINE.md\n+- Status.md\n+- HANDOFF.md\n+- change.md\n+\n+### MUST NOT edit\n+- plans/IMPLEMENTATION.md\n+- crates/editor-shell/**\n+- Any other `crates/**` source, test, bench, fixture, or docs path\n+- Any `editor/**`, `kernel/**`, `runtime/**`, `tools/**`, `docs/**`, or `plans/**`\n+  path other than `plans/BASELINE.md`\n+- Cargo.toml\n+- Cargo.lock\n+- .gitignore\n+- AI_DISPATCH_AUTOMATION.md\n+- ai_handoffs/AI_HANDOFF_PROTOCOL.md\n+- ai_handoffs/templates/**\n+- Any existing ai_handoffs packet, including the POSTV0 packet referenced above\n+\n+### MAY add new files\n+- ai_handoffs/ISSUE-118_EXEC_*.md, the execution report for this dispatch only\n+  if the executor is operating through the handoff protocol. Do not hand-create\n+  sidecars; if the orchestration layer finalizes the EXEC packet, its generated\n+  `.meta.json` sidecar is automation output rather than task content.\n+\n+### MUST NOT add new files\n+- New baseline measurement artifacts\n+- New ADRs, doctrine docs, plans, scripts, schemas, lints, tests, benches, or\n+  fixtures\n+- New source files under any crate or application directory\n+- New Cargo manifests or lockfiles\n+- New ai_handoffs packets other than this dispatch\u0027s own EXEC packet\n+\n+## Deliverables\n+\n+- `plans/BASELINE.md` is revised only enough to stop presenting the non-winit\n+  editor-shell perf harness as currently deferred. It must record that the\n+  harness landed post-v0 at commit `f8b8ed4` in\n+  `crates/editor-shell/src/render_frame_e2e_perf.rs` and must cross-reference\n+  the POSTV0 EXEC packet.\n+- `Status.md` gets a new top prepended snapshot dated 2026-05-23 for ISSUE-118.\n+  Older snapshots must remain in place as historical records.\n+- `HANDOFF.md` gets a new top prepended snapshot dated 2026-05-23 for ISSUE-118.\n+  Older snapshots must remain in place as historical records.\n+- `change.md` gets exactly one new 2026-05-23 entry appended to the existing\n+  chronological history. Do not rewrite old entries.\n+- The docs clearly distinguish the unchanged v0 certification at commit\n+  `6aaf7f1` from the later post-v0 harness landing at commit `f8b8ed4`.\n+\n+## Acceptance Criteria\n+\n+- Only the four allowed documentation files are modified, apart from this\n+  dispatch\u0027s own EXEC packet.\n+- `plans/IMPLEMENTATION.md` is untouched.\n+- No source, test, bench, fixture, Cargo, schema, lint, automation, or protocol\n+  file is touched.\n+- `plans/BASELINE.md` no longer has current-state wording that says the\n+  non-winit editor-shell perf harness remains blocked or deferred. If older\n+  dated context is retained, it must be explicitly framed as historical and\n+  superseded by `f8b8ed4`.\n+- `Status.md` and `HANDOFF.md` preserve existing dated snapshots by prepending\n+  the new snapshot above them. Do not edit old snapshots merely to make them\n+  read current.\n+- `change.md` preserves existing dated entries by appending one new entry. Do\n+  not rewrite the 2026-05-14 v0 certification entry or any other old entry.\n+- The new current records include all three references:\n+  `f8b8ed4`, `crates/editor-shell/src/render_frame_e2e_perf.rs`, and\n+  `ai_handoffs/POSTV0-EDITOR-SHELL-PERF-HARNESS-001_EXEC_2026-05-14_21-51-40+0300.md`.\n+- No new `plans/BASELINE.md` measurement row is added for the editor-shell\n+  harness.\n+- No recorder-host P95/P50/worst-sample measurement numbers are copied from the\n+  POSTV0 EXEC packet into `plans/BASELINE.md`, `Status.md`, `HANDOFF.md`, or\n+  `change.md`.\n+- No new hard P95, worst-sample, or similar performance threshold is chosen for\n+  the editor-shell harness. Threshold pinning remains a future certification\n+  scope unless a separate task explicitly authorizes it.\n+\n+## Constraints / Non-Goals\n+\n+- This is documentation reconciliation only. It does not execute, modify, tune,\n+  or re-measure the editor-shell perf harness.\n+- Do not run the release-only editor-shell perf harness.\n+- Do not run fresh recorder-host measurements.\n+- Do not run Cargo commands of any kind for this dispatch.\n+- Do not change `plans/IMPLEMENTATION.md`, even though stale references may be\n+  mentioned there. The issue scope explicitly excludes it.\n+- Do not claim the post-v0 harness changes the old v0 release certification\n+  commit. The correct framing is: v0 certification remains at `6aaf7f1`; the\n+  editor-shell perf-harness deferral was later resolved by POSTV0 at `f8b8ed4`.\n+- Do not import the POSTV0 measurement table into the baseline docs. Record\n+  existence, path, commit, and packet provenance only.\n+\n+## Verification Gates\n+\n+The Executor MUST run and document the result of each of these in their\n+`EXECUTION_REPORT`. These gates are intentionally docs-only and use no Cargo\n+commands:\n+\n+- `git diff --check -- plans/BASELINE.md Status.md HANDOFF.md change.md`\n+  -\u003e expected exit 0.\n+- `git diff --name-only -- plans/BASELINE.md Status.md HANDOFF.md change.md`\n+  -\u003e expected exactly the four allowed docs when tracked changes are inspected.\n+- `git diff -- plans/IMPLEMENTATION.md`\n+  -\u003e expected empty diff.\n+- `git status --short --untracked-files=all`\n+  -\u003e expected no modified tracked files outside `plans/BASELINE.md`,\n+  `Status.md`, `HANDOFF.md`, and `change.md`, with only this dispatch\u0027s own\n+  ai_handoffs packet(s) allowed as untracked additions.\n+- Manual diff review of the four docs confirms: prepended snapshots in\n+  `Status.md` and `HANDOFF.md`, one appended `change.md` entry, no baseline\n+  measurement row, no copied POSTV0 P95/P50/worst-sample numbers, and no new\n+  editor-shell hard performance threshold.\n+\n+## Halt Conditions\n+\n+The Executor MUST halt without committing and write an EXEC packet with\n+`STATUS: NEEDS_HUMAN`, `HANDOFF_STATUS: NEEDS_HUMAN`, and\n+`NEXT_ROLE: HUMAN_ARBITER` if any of the following occur:\n+\n+- Reconciliation appears to require editing `plans/IMPLEMENTATION.md`.\n+- Reconciliation appears to require editing `crates/editor-shell/**` or any\n+  other source, test, bench, fixture, Cargo, schema, lint, automation, or\n+  protocol file.\n+- The Executor believes a new measurement row, copied recorder-host numbers, or\n+  new hard editor-shell thresholds are necessary to make the docs accurate.\n+- The Executor believes any Cargo command, release-only perf harness run, or\n+  fresh recorder-host measurement is needed.\n+- The four allowed docs contain conflicting history that cannot be reconciled by\n+  adding a current dated snapshot/entry and narrow `plans/BASELINE.md` wording.\n+\n+## Planner Notes\n+\n+Relevant prior record:\n+`ai_handoffs/POSTV0-EDITOR-SHELL-PERF-HARNESS-001_EXEC_2026-05-14_21-51-40+0300.md`\n+states that the POSTV0 editor-shell perf harness dispatch amended the local\n+commit to `f8b8ed4` and that the changed files included\n+`crates/editor-shell/src/render_frame_e2e_perf.rs`. It also states that hard P95\n+threshold pinning was deferred. For ISSUE-118, use that packet as provenance for\n+existence and commit/path only. Do not treat its measurement table as a new\n+`plans/BASELINE.md` baseline row.\n+\n+Known stale current-state wording to reconcile includes the v0 release snapshots\n+that list \"editor-shell mock-event-loop perf harness\" as a known deferral and\n+the `plans/BASELINE.md` Gate A note that describes the non-winit editor-shell\n+perf harness as still deferred. Preserve those old dated records as history in\n+`Status.md`, `HANDOFF.md`, and `change.md`; add current records that supersede\n+them.\n+\n+---\n+\n+HANDOFF_STATUS: COMPLETE\n+DISPATCH_ID: ISSUE-118\n+AUTHOR: Planner / OpenAI Codex\n+NEXT_ROLE: EXECUTOR_AI\n+EXIT_CODE: 0\n+\n+---"
