        "patch":  "@@ -1628,3 +1628,5 @@ ew / partial / is_full_revolution / existing geometry tests. **Critical design c\n 2026-05-21 (Phase 9 editor-usability preflight â€” read-only audit of the editor\u0027s user-facing surface recorded in `plans/BASELINE.md`, IMPLEMENTED): docs-only, single primary file (`plans/BASELINE.md`) + this change-log entry. Appends a new `## Editor-usability preflight (Phase 9)` section directly under the Â§1.1 reflection-scale preflight that landed in commit `f308ce2`. Audits what a user can actually do today in the `rge-editor` binary against IMPLEMENTATION.md Â§9\u0027s \"Editor usability â€” friction points from real authoring\" axis, using read-only inspection of `editor-shell` / `editor-ui` / `editor-actions` / `editor-state` / `components-editor` / `anim-graph-editor` / `material-graph-editor` plus grep over file-extension string literals, `CommandBus::submit` call sites, `KeyboardInput` event branches, and `io-gltf` / `io-image` / `io-3mf` public-API call sites. **Headline findings**: (a) the `rge-editor` binary entry point is `editor/rge-editor/src/main.rs:38-96` (one hardcoded `CuboidOp(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)` constructed and rendered via `EditorShell::with_world_projection_graph`); (b) 8 workflows work end-to-end today â€” launch + render hardcoded cuboid, mouse cursor tracking, left-click face picking + orange highlight overlay (sub-Îµ), Play/Stop/Pause/Step PIE byte-identical-snapshot, editor-coord state persists across Play/Stop, workspace layout RON persistence (egui_dock), render handoff latest-only, time-scale dilation â€” all with file:line citations; (c) **312 `#[test]` annotations across `editor-*` crates** (74 integration / 238 unit) cover the *internals* well but have **no coverage** of the full UI event loop (mouse clicks / keyboard input through `window_event`), WASM script reload via editor, multi-entity scene complexity, or fillet/loft operator-graph UX flow. **Top 3 usability gaps recorded**: (1) **no scene/project persistence** â€” zero `open_file` / `load_project` / `save_project` symbols, zero `.rge` / `.rgeproj` / `.scene` / `.project` extension matches, `rge-data` RON serializer never called by editor; the authoring loop is structurally unmeasurable because there is no loop to friction-test; (2) **Command Bus is fully implemented but structurally unreachable from the editor UI** â€” `crates/editor-actions/src/bus.rs:86,143` defines `CommandBus::submit` with full `UndoStack` + 500ms-coalesce + audit-ledger plumbing and 23 unit tests, but zero call sites from `editor-shell` / `rge-editor` dispatch any user-triggered command through the bus, and `lifecycle.rs:776` catch-all `_ =\u003e {}` silently swallows every `KeyboardInput` event; (3) **`MenuRegistry` + `io-*` asset loaders both ready internally but never called from the editor** â€” `MenuRegistry::resolve` produces `ResolvedEntry` values that no editor-shell code acts on, `io-gltf::import_glb` / `io-image::load_path` / `io-image::load_bytes` have zero call sites from the editor surface, no drag-drop, no CLI file arg. Cross-cutting pattern: substrate-first architecture has worked but no user-input path connects any closed subsystem to a visible scene change; the editor today is a rendering + picking testbed with battle-tested internals nobody can drive from the UI. **Rejected/boundedness note for the F â†’ `SpawnCuboidAt` proposal**: a candidate follow-up to wire `F` â†’ `Command::SpawnCuboidAt(Vec3)` through `CommandBus::submit` â†’ spawn a second cuboid + `Ctrl+Z` â†’ `CommandBus::undo()` with a headless test was considered and **rejected as not bounded**. Verified `CommandBus::submit(action: Box\u003cdyn Action\u003e, world: \u0026mut World)` at `bus.rs:143`, `Action::apply(\u0026self, world: \u0026mut World)` at `action.rs:87`, `Action::revert(\u0026self, world: \u0026mut World)` at `action.rs:96` â€” the `Action` trait is **World-only** and has no access to `CadGraph` / `CadProjection` / editor-shell render projection state. A visible CAD-cuboid spawn requires mutating `CadGraph` and producing a fresh `CadProjection` snapshot, neither of which lives in `World`; the current cuboid is constructed in `editor/rge-editor/src/main.rs:47-68` against standalone `CadGraph` + `CadProjection` instances handed to `EditorShell` once at construction time via `with_world_projection_graph`, and the render path is explicitly single-cuboid / sub-Î´ scope. Landing F â†’ `SpawnCuboidAt` as a \"small\" dispatch would force either a CommandBus context redesign (changing the World-only invariant on which 23 `editor-actions` tests rely) or a parallel \"editor command\" channel that forks the architecture and the audit-ledger story. **Defer code until a separate CommandBus integration design dispatch decides whether the bus stays `(\u0026mut World)`-only or grows a richer context** (e.g. `(\u0026mut World, \u0026mut CadGraph, \u0026mut CadProjection)` or a typed `\u0026mut EditorCommandCtx`), and what the corresponding `Action::apply` / `revert` signature looks like â€” that design dispatch can itself be docs-only (ADR / design note plus a stub adapter); it does not have to land the full multi-context bus. **Two-arm revisit trigger** codified: re-run this preflight when **either** (a) a CommandBus integration design dispatch lands a decision on the bus\u0027s command-context shape, **or** (b) a non-CAD user-input path lands first (e.g. `Ctrl+S` / `Ctrl+O` bound to the working workspace-layout RON load/save substrate per `workspace_round_trip.rs`, or PIE Play/Stop bound to a keyboard shortcut) and forces the catch-all at `lifecycle.rs:776` to grow a real `KeyboardInput` branch without first redesigning the bus. Until **at least one** of those fires, **defer all user-facing editor wire-up dispatches**. Also rejected for the same architectural-cost reason: `Ctrl+S` workspace-RON-only (ships a half-loop with no `Ctrl+O` partner); `--load \u003cgltf-path\u003e` CLI arg (foreign-mesh-into-editor ingestion is